Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.66,0:06:28.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人马座A\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Centaurus A
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.66,0:06:32.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个发射出大量电波的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a galaxy sending out  massive amounts of radio waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.67,0:06:36.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像是星际的广播站\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}think it as a interstellar broadcaster
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.67,0:06:40.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向宇宙日夜不停地发射信号 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}beaming its signal throughout the Universe all day, every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.68,0:06:46.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是最近的活跃星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the closest of the so called active galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.68,0:06:50.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从核心倾泻大量能量的星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Galaxies that pour out tremendous amounts of energy from their cores.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.69,0:06:57.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一幅哈勃超深空图片 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is a Hubble ultra deep field image,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.69,0:06:59.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由哈勃天文望远镜拍摄 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}created using the Hubble space telescope,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.69,0:07:03.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它展示了广裹无垠的宇宙 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it shows us how truly vast and distant the Universe really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.70,0:07:09.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,远方的宇宙不只是空旷 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And how those far spaces are anything but empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.71,0:07:14.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当你看宇宙的非常深处时 你看到的是以前的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you look very deeply in the Universe, you're looking back in the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.71,0:07:18.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以看到的星系都是很久很久以前的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you're looking back galaxies, right back when they were very very young
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.71,0:07:22.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有现在年代几个百分点时的景象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when they're only few percent of their current age.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.72,0:07:25.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哈勃超深空图片就像是时间隧道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the Hubble ultra deep field is like the time tunnel
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.72,0:07:29.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给了我们一个地球诞生前星系的景象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gives us a glimpse of galaxies as they were before the Earth was in existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.73,0:07:32.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球有四十亿年的历史 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth is 4 billion years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.73,0:07:36.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为星系有一百三十亿年的历史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we think galaxies as they were 13 billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.73,0:07:39.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光线离开那些天体时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the light left these objects
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.73,0:07:42.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的星球还不存在 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before there was any earth at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.74,0:07:45.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,靠近我们的大星系 仙女座星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The nearest large galaxy to us, the Andromeda galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.74,0:07:48.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有两百万光年远 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's about 2 million light years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.74,0:07:51.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从仙女座星系来的光 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the light from the Andromeda galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.75,0:07:53.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要用两百万年才到这儿 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}takes 2 million years to get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.75,0:07:56.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以 我们看到的是两百万年前的样子 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so we're seeing it as it looked, 2 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.75,0:07:59.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是最近的星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that is one our nearby galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.75,0:08:01.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们看更遥远的空间 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As we look farther, farther out the space
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.76,0:08:05.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们会看到更遥远的过去 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we will look farther, and farther back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.77,0:08:14.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了更好的理解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To get better idea of the concept,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.77,0:08:18.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去参观地球最为壮观的景色之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just visit one of the most spectacular vistas on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.77,0:08:22.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄伟的大峡谷 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Majestic Great Canyon
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.78,0:08:28.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当观察较低的层时会看到久远的岩石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As you look down the layers you get older and older rocks
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.78,0:08:32.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能辫别不同的环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we can tell what the different environments were.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.81,0:08:38.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以准确了解这儿的地质史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so we can actually look at the geologic history of this area over time and in essence look back
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.79,0:08:44.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过这儿的环境了解数亿年前的地球史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through the environment that was located right here back over hundreds of millions of years in the Earth's history.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.80,0:08:48.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,观察距离地球很远很远的星辰 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, by look at stars further and further away from the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.80,0:08:53.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家可以找到宇宙进化的线索 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the astronomers can get an idea of the evolution of the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.81,0:08:59.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从早期的星系天文学始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From the earliest days of galactic astronomy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.81,0:09:01.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,观察者就已经注意到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}observers noticed galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.82,0:09:05.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系在形状和大小上有着多样性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}came in a variety of shapes and sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.82,0:09:08.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,主要有两种 螺旋星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The two main types of galaxy are spiral galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.82,0:09:12.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像是银河 薄碟形有螺旋臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like our Milky Way, which have spiral arms in a thin disc.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.83,0:09:16.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,椭圆的星系 象球形或椭圆形\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And elliptical galaxies, which sort of more spherical or elliptically shape,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.83,0:09:19.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有螺旋臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they don't have spiral arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:22.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,螺旋星系中有大量的气体和灰尘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spiral galaxies have a lot of gas and dust in them
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.84,0:09:25.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正在形成新的星体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for which new stars forming right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.84,0:09:27.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,椭圆星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Whereas the elliptical galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.84,0:09:30.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,象是星体形成好久了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}seems to formed their stars long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.85,0:09:34.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有大量的气体和灰尘 新的星体不再形成 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They don't have that much gas and dust so they are not forming stars right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.85,0:09:36.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有不规则的星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are also irregular galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.85,0:09:40.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通常他们有大量气体和灰尘但不是螺旋状的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which generally have a lot of gas and dust but not in a nice spiral form.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.86,0:09:48.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,观察遥远处星辰的沉积物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Detecting these far off accumulations of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.86,0:09:50.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成了简单工作 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is made easier when the astronomers
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.87,0:09:52.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在天文学家研究灯塔爆破流时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}search the streaming blasting beacons
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.87,0:09:56.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在爆破流中心的附近找到许多沉积物 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}found near the center of many of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.87,0:10:01.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很多星系的中心都在激烈动荡中 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Violent and erratic hearts beat at the center of many alien galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.88,0:10:04.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,散发出很多能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sending out so much energy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.88,0:10:07.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生的能量胜过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they can overwhelm the amount of energy produced
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.88,0:10:10.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其星系所有恒星产生能量的总和\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by all of other stars within them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.89,0:10:14.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们有活跃的核心 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are the active galactic nuclei.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.89,0:10:18.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们可以看到一些星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we can look at some galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.89,0:10:20.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们发现星系拥有强大的中心化的动力 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we find that they have at their very centers, very powerful engines
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.90,0:10:24.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生了大量的光 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are producing a tremendous amount of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.90,0:10:27.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道它们是非常遥远的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can tell they are far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.90,0:10:29.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使这样 我们观察到的光也是很耀眼 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and yet they are still very bright when you look them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.90,0:10:31.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可见它们有很强的能量 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so they must tremendously powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.91,0:10:35.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每秒都要爆发出大量的能量 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dumping a lot of energy out every second.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.91,0:10:40.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,活跃星系有剧烈和有力核心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Amount the most violent and powerful of the active galactic nuclei
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.92,0:10:44.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个神秘的现象叫 类星体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the mysterious phenomena called quasares.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.92,0:10:50.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当我们观察类星体时 类星体星状物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we look at quasares, quasar stellar objects
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.93,0:10:54.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看它们有多远 有些非常耀眼 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and see how far away they are, some of them tremendously bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.93,0:10:55.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最亮的一个 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The brightest one
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.93,0:10:59.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比我们的太阳要耀眼一万亿倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it about a trillion of times as bright as our sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.93,0:11:03.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,惊人的电磁能量流 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Spectacular streams of electromagnetic energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.94,0:11:07.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,灯塔般照亮数百万英里的天空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}right beacons lighting of the sky for billions miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.94,0:11:11.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些高能源向我们展示了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These high energy sources provide a stunning reminder
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.95,0:11:15.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙的能量 照明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the Universe's power to illuminate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.95,0:11:20.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体自己可能比整个星系都亮 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A quasar itself can be brighter than entire galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.96,0:11:24.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当我们观看类星体象C273的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, when we look at a quasar like 3 C 273
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.96,0:11:26.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用哈勃天文望远镜拍摄的景象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Hubble space telescope took some images of this
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.96,0:11:30.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们发现它喷发出大量的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we found it has big jet of material shooting out beside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.97,0:11:34.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎与星系相仿 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}almost the size of the galaxy itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.97,0:11:38.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,活跃星系核 真是奇怪 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These is really weird things, these active galactic nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.98,0:11:44.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,活跃星系核显示 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As active galactic nucleus show,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.98,0:11:48.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太空是剧烈变化的地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}space is a violent place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.99,0:11:55.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有将要发生的大碰撞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And as it turns out there is a massive collision going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.99,0:12:02.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在我们自己院儿里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}right in our own backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.00,0:12:08.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,罪魁祸首 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The culprit,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.00,0:12:12.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大犬座矮星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a galaxy called the Canis major dwarf galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.01,0:12:18.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就名字而言 矮星系就是小星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the name implies dwarfed galaxies are small.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.01,0:12:22.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以很难被发现 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}making them even more difficult to detect.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.02,0:12:34.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在大犬座矮星系正朝着银河运动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, the Canis major dwarf galaxy is taking aim at the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.03,0:12:41.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两星系发生冲突是引力的原因 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Two galaxies on a collision course from which, thanks to the gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.04,0:12:46.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无法逃避\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there is no escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.04,0:12:51.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当小的星系接近大星系时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When a small galaxy comes too close a large galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.05,0:12:56.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,潮汐作用可使其被拉伸和扭曲 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the tidal effects can cause it to be stretched out and distorted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.05,0:13:00.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以大星系的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the gravitational attraction of the larger galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.05,0:13:04.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将会推压小星系内的星体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will actually pull and stretch the stars in the smaller galaxy.
