Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.92,0:26:28.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接着我们发现太阳是许多恒星中的一员 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then we discovered that our Sun was one of many stars
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.01,0:26:32.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,据我们所知 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and our sun was cruising around through the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.36,0:26:33.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的太阳在宇宙中巡航 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as we knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.93,0:26:37.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但哈勃的发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But this discovery by Hubble
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.44,0:26:40.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,告诉我们 不只我们的行星是众多行星中的一员 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}told us that not only was our planet one of many planets
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.62,0:26:43.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的恒星太阳是众多恒星中的一员 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and our star, the sun, was one of many stars
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.42,0:26:45.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且我们的星系和行星 太阳一样 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but that our galaxy was one of many galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.91,0:26:46.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也是众多星系中的一员 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}presumable like many others.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.38,0:26:57.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的世界观和在宇宙的位置变了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It really changed our world view and our place in the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.42,0:27:01.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的星系不过是普通的一个星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to think that our galaxy is an ordinary galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.78,0:27:06.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我们看看谁是我们的星系邻居？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So just what's in our galactic neighbourhood?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.11,0:27:09.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,认识一下我们的紧邻 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Meet the local group of galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.84,0:27:12.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一群还在增加的成员 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A group with ever increasing membership.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.78,0:27:18.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们附近的星系群是个小群 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our local group of galaxies is a small group
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.38,0:27:21.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这群大约有三打星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or a cluster of about 3 dozen galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.95,0:27:26.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们银河系和仙女座星系 M31\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Milky Way and the Andromeda galaxy, M31
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.28,0:27:28.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是两个绩优星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are the two dominant galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.52,0:27:30.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系群中其它的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}most of the galaxies in our local group
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.48,0:27:32.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都是矮星星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are small dwarf galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.78,0:27:43.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些星系都有几个小的卫星星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These galaxies each have collections of small satellite galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.78,0:27:46.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,象奴隶一样围绕着它们 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are in their thrall. that orbit around them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.22,0:27:52.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大的星系之间都受到对方的引力影响 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And these big galaxies all feel the influence of each other's masses
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.32,0:27:54.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相互绕行 所有的星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and orbit around each other. So all of these galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.97,0:27:57.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小的绕着大的转 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the small galaxies are orbiting the big galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.25,0:27:59.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大的相互绕着转 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and big galaxies are also orbiting echo other.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.52,0:28:02.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个有三十多个星系的星系群 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's a group of about 30 or more galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.64,0:28:05.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,围绕着它们共同的质量中心旋转 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that all orbit around a common center mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.97,0:28:12.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我们星系群的两个著名的矮星星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The most well known dwarf members of the local group,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.11,0:28:17.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是大 小麦哲伦星云 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}two galaxies known as Large and Small Magellanic clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.60,0:28:28.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家现在认为 受银河系引力影响 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists now think the clouds orbit the Milky Way
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.50,0:28:31.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们在围绕着银河系旋转 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thanks to the tidal influence of our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.51,0:28:40.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引力是双刃剑 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity of course is a two way street.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.44,0:28:44.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以认为来自星云的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's believe the gravitational pull from these clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.75,0:28:48.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同样扭曲了我们星系的部分圆盘 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has also distorted parts of our own galactic disc.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.00,0:28:55.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由恒星释放出的能量测定 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By measuring the energy it emits from the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.33,0:28:58.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大 小麦哲伦星云 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the Small and Large Magellanic clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.68,0:29:01.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家认为 它们的组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}astronomers believe they are made of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.46,0:29:03.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和我们的星系不同 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}different stuff than our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.09,0:29:09.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相对银河系 星云中富含氢和氦 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The clouds are richer in hydrogen and helium than the Milky Way
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.02,0:29:12.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,金属含量少 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and with fewer metals.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.02,0:29:20.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家认为这表明 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists think this means
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.76,0:29:22.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星云中的恒星是新星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the stars are younger in the clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.62,0:29:34.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星云和银河系之间的引力舞蹈 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gravitational dance between the clouds and Milky Way
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.47,0:29:38.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看起来进行了数亿年了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has likely be going on for billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.66,0:29:44.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时一种不同的和更加神秘的战斗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But all the while, a different and much more mysterious battle
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.32,0:29:48.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发生在银河系的中心 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is going on back in the center of  Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.32,0:29:58.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当你到了银河系的中心 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because when you head for the center of our galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.44,0:30:02.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,穿过了宇宙灰尘 气体和星辰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}once you get through all the dust, gas and all the older stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.96,0:30:06.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会发现大吃一惊的东西 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you find something so insanely frighting
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.55,0:30:10.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时间和空间的正常规则在这儿是不适用的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the normal rules of time and space do not apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.85,0:30:20.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在银河的中心或许在每个星系的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For lurking at the heart of Milky Way and perhaps every alien galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.09,0:30:25.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是一个有贪婪的胃口的超级怪兽 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a massive beast with a ravenous appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.05,0:30:31.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个无法逃脱的怪兽 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A beast from which there is no escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.49,0:30:46.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我们的星系--银河系的核心区域 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is a region at the core of our galaxy, the Milky Way
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.71,0:30:49.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里什么都无法逃脱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where nothing escapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.52,0:30:54.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里有去无回 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the point of no return
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.05,0:30:57.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个巨大的超级黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a super massive black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.28,0:31:10.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞是一种天体物理学物体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A black hole is an astrophysical object,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.96,0:31:14.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有巨大的质量 微小的体积 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that has so much mass, in such a small volume
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.92,0:31:17.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的引力非常强大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the gravitational force is so strong
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.29,0:31:20.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就连光也没有足够的能量逃脱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that even light doesn't have enough energy to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.84,0:31:24.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞形成于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Black holes can form
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.73,0:31:28.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者巨大的恒星生命终止时的爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}either when massive stars explode at the end of its life
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.87,0:31:36.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其核心崩溃成为黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the core of the star collapses into a black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.87,0:31:47.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者在星系的中心形成黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or you can have super massive black holes at the centers of the galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.55,0:31:56.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多么大？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How massive?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.25,0:32:01.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,设想一下接近400万倍的太阳的质量 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Try nearly 4 million times the mass of our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.09,0:32:11.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时候黑洞吞噬整个恒星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sometimes black holes swallow entire stars
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.87,0:32:16.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引发剧烈爆炸产生伽玛射线暴 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creating fierce explosions called gamma ray bursts.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.80,0:32:18.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要产生伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In order to emit a gamma ray,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.83,0:32:22.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,物体的温度要达到几十亿度 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an object has to be billions of degree in temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.02,0:32:26.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者万亿度 不可置信地热 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or even trillions, so we're seeing something incredibly hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.93,0:32:31.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时候一百亿光年外的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In some cases the galaxies were as much as 10 billion light years away
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.27,0:32:35.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生伽玛射线暴时亮到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the gamma ray bursts had been so bright
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.79,0:32:37.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用副望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that if you had a pair of binoculars
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.34,0:32:40.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在正确的时间和正确的角度 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you were actually looking at right part of the sky at the right time
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.43,0:32:44.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就可以看到伽玛射线暴的余晖 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you would have been able to see visible afterglow of the gamma rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.40,0:32:46.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就用望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's using binoculars
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.16,0:32:49.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看到宇宙那边的景物 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to see something that's on the other side of the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.24,0:32:51.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一百亿光年外呀 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}10 billion light years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.54,0:32:55.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你能想象到那是什么样的爆炸吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Can you imagine what sort of explosion that was?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.64,0:33:10.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,假如我们的星系中心有个巨大的超级黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if there is a super massive black hole at the center of our galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.71,0:33:12.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相同的黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are similar black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.92,0:33:15.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在每个星系中心都有吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}located at center of all alien galaxies?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.07,0:33:20.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当观察相邻星系的时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we look at neighboring galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.90,0:33:22.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最近的结果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this is a recent result
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.71,0:33:24.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们看到大部分星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we find that most galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.02,0:33:27.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中心有个巨大的超级黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}seem to have very massive black holes in the center
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.57,0:33:30.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,范围是数百万甚至数亿倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that range from millions even billion times
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.00,0:33:31.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的太阳的质量 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as much as our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.49,0:33:36.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这对星系来说似乎很常见和普通\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It appears to be a very common and ordinary aspect of a galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.91,0:33:50.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞吞噬物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Black holes swallow matter
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.37,0:33:56.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但宇宙1%的一少半\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but less than one half of 1 % of our Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.00,0:33:59.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相信是可以观察到的物质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's believed to be made up of observable matter
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.01,0:34:04.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,象恒星 行星 气体和星尘 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}such as the stars, planets, gas and dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.15,0:34:14.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大爆炸后形成的物质如何运作？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So what accounts for the rest stuff created in aftermath of the Big Bang?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.11,0:34:24.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到底是什么形成了星系？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What really fills up alien galaxies?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.19,0:34:27.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家的最佳推测 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A scientist's best guess
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.80,0:34:30.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是种神秘物质--暗物质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a mysterious substance call dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.59,0:34:36.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,暗物质是神奇的东西 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark matter is fantastic stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.09,0:34:41.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道它存在 我们知道它在吸引物质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know that it exists, we know that it gravitationally pulls on things.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.41,0:34:46.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,暗黑物质存在的最佳证据之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the best pieces of evidences for the existence of dark matter
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.59,0:34:49.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是螺旋星系的自转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that spiral galaxies are spinning
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.08,0:34:52.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比它们应有的速度快 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}more quickly than they would be spinning
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.29,0:34:55.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除非有看不到的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}unless there were extra unseeing material
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.75,0:34:58.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,导致它们的自转加速 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}causing them to spin that fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.96,0:35:09.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,加州理工的埃利斯教授用一项新技术创新地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Caltech professor Richard Ellis has pioneered a new technique
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.01,0:35:13.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,建立了宇宙的三唯地图 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to create a three-dimensional map of the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.24,0:35:15.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,包括暗物质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including the dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.39,0:35:21.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是首次由动态数据给出的暗示 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the first hint from dynamical data
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.24,0:35:24.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙中存在大量的暗物质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that there's a lot of dark matter in the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.18,0:35:27.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们也可通过非凡的现象发现暗物质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can also detect dark matter by really remarkable phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.03,0:35:31.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是由爱因斯坦预测 现在被天文学应用的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is predicted by Einstein and is now in great in astronomy
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.81,0:35:34.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引力透镜效应 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which we call gravitational lensing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.31,0:35:40.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,暗物质使通过它的光线弯曲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark matter bends light passing through it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.01,0:35:44.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很象块不平的玻璃 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}much like a curved piece of glass
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.07,0:35:48.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光波被物质弯曲 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The light rays are bent by material
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.98,0:35:53.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在哪里看到这种弯曲的光线 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and where we can see the signature of this bending of the light rays
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.02,0:35:56.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是说那里就有大量暗物质的存在 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can infer that there's lot of dark matter present.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.97,0:35:59.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们无法直接看到暗物质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We don't have to see the dark matter directly
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.24,0:36:01.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它既不发光也不反光 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it doesn't shine, it doesn't scatter light
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.41,0:36:05.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我们可以推测它的存在 通过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we can infer its presence from the effect it has
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.67,0:36:07.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,穿过暗物质的光线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on light rays that are coming
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.52,0:36:09.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所受到的它的影响 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through the clump of dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.73,0:36:12.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们知道暗物质的存在 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, we know the dark matter is there
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.03,0:36:14.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能画它的分布图 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can make maps of how it is distributed
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.34,0:36:17.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管我们无法直接看到 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even if we cannot see it directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.99,0:36:20.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引力透镜效应更大的优势\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So one farther advantage of gravitational lensing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.82,0:36:23.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是它像放大镜一样 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it is it just like a magnifying glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.88,0:36:26.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过它观察的时 想对于没有它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So when you look through it, things are bigger and brighter
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.56,0:36:28.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,物体会大点儿 亮点儿 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than they would be if you didn't have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.06,0:36:33.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以认为它是太空中天然的望远镜 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if you think about it, it's like a natural telescope in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.21,0:36:39.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管暗物质的作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While dark matter plays a central role
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.62,0:36:42.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在星系的诞生和进化很重要 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the birth and evolving life of the galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.71,0:36:46.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有一种暗力量起了部分作用 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there is another dark force partially responsible for its growth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.41,0:36:52.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以宇宙角度来看 星系在快速远离我们而去 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On a cosmic scale, the galaxies are rushing away from us
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.50,0:36:55.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为宇宙在不停的膨胀 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}due to the continuing expansion of the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.78,0:37:00.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果宇宙在膨胀 什么力量推动它的澎胀？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, if the Universe is expanding, what's driving it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.11,0:37:05.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在科学家只有一种答案 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The only answer scientists can come up with for now
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.21,0:37:07.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种神秘的暗能量 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a mysterious dark energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.51,0:37:13.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,暗能量某种角度上比暗物质还要怪 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark energy is even stranger in some ways than dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.41,0:37:16.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,暗能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark energy
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.49,0:37:21.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,导致了宇宙膨胀一直到现在 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is causing the Universe to expand right now
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.12,0:37:24.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随时间越来越快 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}faster and faster with time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.12,0:37:32.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个宇宙概念的膨胀运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This expansion set in motion at the Universe's conception
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.42,0:37:35.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已被加速了数十亿年了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has accelerated in the last few billion years
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.52,0:37:40.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为暗能量 发起的运动随时间增长而增长 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the dark energy that creates the movement has increased over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.02,0:37:49.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自然地 维系星系们联系的引力 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By nature, the gravitational force they binds galaxies together
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.12,0:37:54.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着它们之间的距离增加逐渐减弱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}decrease over time as the space between them increases.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.62,0:37:59.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是增加引力 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, instead of having a gravitational pull
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.30,0:38:02.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是减缓宇宙的膨胀 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}instead of slowing down the expansion of the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.82,0:38:06.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,暗能量在加速宇宙的膨胀 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dark energy is speeding up the expansion of the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.02,0:38:11.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且已经加速了四 五十亿年了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it has been doing that for the passing 4 or 5 billion of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.52,0:38:18.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经过或许数十亿 数万亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In perhaps a billion, trillion more years
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.02,0:38:22.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙的命运和对它的影响 黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the fate of the Universe and the impact, the black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.22,0:38:23.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dark matter
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.72,0:38:25.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和暗能量终会被人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and dark energy have on the mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.22,0:38:28.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所了解 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will finally be known.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.62,0:38:43.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当一颗恒星离黑洞太近时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When a star get too close to a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.82,0:38:48.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系的中心将会出现混乱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the heart of an alien galaxy, chaos arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.92,0:39:03.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是又一个探索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's one of the findings for
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.52,0:39:05.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系进化的任务 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the galaxies evolution explorer mission
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.42,0:39:06.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,简称 加里克 (星系演化探测器).\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or GALEX (GALaxies Evolution eXplorer).
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.42,0:39:20.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,加里克是一架紫外线望远镜 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Galaxy Evolution Explorer is an ultraviolet telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.12,0:39:24.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用来观测宇宙的紫外线波长 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that observes the Universe in ultraviolet wavelengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.02,0:39:28.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些波长非常敏感于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And at these wavelengths you are very sensitive
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.72,0:39:30.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新星的研究 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to studying young stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.52,0:39:33.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,敏感于星系中恒星的形成 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stars formation in the galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.62,0:39:37.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,回到宇宙年龄一半的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}back to half the age of universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.42,0:39:39.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数十亿年以前 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}billions of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.22,0:39:44.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然也要观测那些发光火焰的紫外线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, we also look in ultraviolet for these luminous flames
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.22,0:39:48.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发出于被黑洞吞噬的恒星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from when a star is swallowed by a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.80,0:39:51.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当恒星再也坚持不住时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The star can't hold itself together anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.10,0:39:54.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它被肢解了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it is ripped apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.20,0:39:57.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从恒星来的气体陷入了黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the gas from the star plunges into the black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.60,0:40:01.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些气体会被高速甩出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of the gas would be ejected from the system at high velocities
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.20,0:40:06.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但大部份气体会陷入了黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but some fraction of the gas will plunge into the black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.50,0:40:10.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个过程将被加热到极高温度 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in that process will heat up to very high temperatures
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.50,0:40:15.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,散发出发光火焰的紫外线和X射线 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and give off a luminous flame of ultraviolet and X-ray radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.50,0:40:22.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,感谢加里克  苏维·吉扎里和其他的研究者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thanks to the GALEX, Suvi Gezari and other researches
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.50,0:40:24.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were able to watch all happened
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.00,0:40:27.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,四十亿光年之外发生的事情 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}4 billion light years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.00,0:40:39.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,加里克--哈勃和史匹哲不久会有个新邻居\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Galex, Hubble and the Spitzer space telescope will soon be get a new neighbor
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.20,0:40:43.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用来拍摄星系的图片 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}designed to help catch images of alien galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.80,0:40:49.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,韦伯太空望远镜定于2013年发射 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The James Webb space telescope is due to launch in 2013
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.40,0:40:53.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用于探索红外光谱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}designed to explore the infrared spectrum
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.20,0:40:54.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开一先河 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like never before.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.20,0:40:59.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使用韦伯望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Using the Webb telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.20,0:41:03.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家希望可以穿过恒星和星尘的遮挡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists hope to be able to see through dust and the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.71,0:41:06.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看到银河系的中心 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that block our view of the Milky Way center.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.20,0:41:09.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,获得更为清晰的图片 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and provide more complete picture
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.20,0:41:10.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不只是我们的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not just our galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.20,0:41:13.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且所有的星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but of all alien galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.60,0:41:21.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,韦伯太空望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The James Webb space telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.18,0:41:23.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和哈勃望远镜有两方面不同 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}differs from the Hubble space telescope in two aspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.30,0:41:26.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第一 更强大 其有一个更大的反射镜 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Firstly, it's more powerful, it has a greater mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.82,0:41:29.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其次 它可以工作于略长的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Secondly, it is actually working at slightly longer
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.02,0:41:31.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红外线波长 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}infrared waves lengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.50,0:41:35.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哈勃和韦伯它们共同的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What Hubble and Webb have in common
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.80,0:41:39.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是脱离了流动大气的影响 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the power to see beyond atmospheric turbulence
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.80,0:41:43.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,流动大气使天文学家得不到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that prevent astronomers to get picture perfect images
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.10,0:41:45.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,99 % 的天空的完美图片 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from 99 % of the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.10,0:41:49.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球大气是动荡的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth atmosphere is turbulent.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.30,0:41:54.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它影响了恒星发出的光 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It blows out the images from stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.30,0:41:58.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果地球没有大气 我们看到的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if the Earth had no atmosphere we would see stars basically
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.80,0:42:01.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会是完美的光点 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}really perfect dots of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.00,0:42:04.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是光在通过大气的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what happens is that because light passes through the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.91,0:42:07.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发生弯曲 变成分散的光斑 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's distorted, it turns into a fuzz blob.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.11,0:42:10.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有两个办法解决这个问题 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It turns out there are two ways to fix this.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.11,0:42:12.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个是到太空去 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One way is to go the space
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.41,0:42:17.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一个不是处理地上的望远镜 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the other way is to instead fix the telescope on the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.71,0:42:20.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是消除大气带来的影响 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that it removes the effect of the turbulence
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.41,0:42:23.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这项技术就是自适应光学测量法 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that is a technology know as Adaptive optics.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.41,0:42:28.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自适应光学测量星系影像的方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Adaptive optics measures the image of a galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.01,0:42:32.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是消除光线对其他发光体的反射 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the way its light reflects off another lighting object
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.31,0:42:34.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如附近的明亮的恒星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like nearby bright star.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.81,0:42:39.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自适应光学需要很亮的恒星作参照 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To do Adaptive optics sensing you need a very bright star
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.49,0:42:41.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然在大气中测量时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because of course, you are making measurements of the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.51,0:42:43.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每秒要达到数百次甚至上千次 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hundreds or thousands of times per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.21,0:42:44.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,需要很亮的东西作参照 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so you need something bright look it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.84,0:42:48.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大部分恒星都不够亮 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most stars are not bright enough to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.84,0:42:51.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以在柯奇工作的夏威夷天文台\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At observatories like the Keck in Hawaii
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.84,0:42:53.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自适应光学系统要使用激光束 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Adaptive optics uses a laser beam
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.85,0:42:57.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,提供拍摄时的光的需求 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to help create the light needed for the snap shoots.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.85,0:43:00.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以用它指到天空中任何一点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can point anywhere you want on the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.85,0:43:04.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不只是1%的天空 你可看到绝大部分天空 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so instead of looking at only 1% of the sky, you can look at most of the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.86,0:43:08.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,得到非常高的分辫率的清晰图像 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a very very high resolution, very sharp images.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.86,0:43:12.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用这个方法 能提升图片10到20倍的清晰度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In this way you can make images 10-20 times sharper from the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.87,0:43:16.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,参照于不使用自适应光学\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than you could without adaptive optics.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.87,0:43:18.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们设计的另一个工具\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's just another tool in the kit of course designed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.87,0:43:22.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为将奇异的其它星系的图片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to bring the fantastic reaches of alien galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.88,0:43:26.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带回地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}back down to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.88,0:43:31.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙 当然\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Universe, of course
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.88,0:43:35.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,万物之家 比我们的地球大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is home to many things larger than our small planet Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.89,0:43:38.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比我们的太阳系大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}larger than our Solar System
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.89,0:43:41.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比我们银河系大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}larger than our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.89,0:43:42.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想想我们的银河 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To think that our Milky Way
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.90,0:43:45.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是可探测的宇宙中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is just one of hundreds billions galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.90,0:43:47.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上千亿个星系之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the observable Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.90,0:43:51.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以这样想 我们是比地球大好多的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's really feels like you are part of something much larger
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.90,0:43:55.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,东西的一部分 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than our small planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.91,0:43:59.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无论你是否喜欢 这就是我们在宇宙的地位 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like or not this is our place in the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.91,0:44:05.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一点一点地累积 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A speck on a speck on a speck.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.92,0:44:08.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小小的蓝色地球 生命绿洲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just one tiny blue green oasis of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.92,0:44:13.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,遨游在浩瀚的星系海洋中 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}swimming in a vast ocean of alien galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.00,0:44:25.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢观赏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thanks For Viewing
